    "score" : 26,
    "last_activity_date" : 1485106882,
    "last_edit_date" : 1485106882,
    "creation_date" : 1431328342,
    "answer_id" : 30161602,
    "question_id" : 22756153,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><strong>Adding the Tomcat server in the server runtime will do the job:</strong></p>\n\n<p><em>Project Properties</em> → <em>Target Runtimes</em> → Select your Server from the list, \"JBoss Runtime\" → <kbd>Finish</kbd></p>\n\n<p>In case of Apache you can select Apache Runtime.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/9yBnq.png\" alt=\"Enter image description here\"></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1864866,
      "reputation" : 960,
      "user_id" : 1688683,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 36,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/yY34N.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Puneet Pandey",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1688683/puneet-pandey"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1485106929,
    "last_edit_date" : 1485106929,
    "creation_date" : 1433238604,
    "answer_id" : 30592708,
    "question_id" : 22756153,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>And if nothing works by whatever reason, build it from the command line:</p>\n\n<pre><code>ant -Dj2ee.server.home=D:\\apache-tomcat-8.0.23 clean\n\nant -Dj2ee.server.home=D:\\apache-tomcat-8.0.23 compile\n\nant -Dj2ee.server.home=D:\\apache-tomcat-8.0.23 dist\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1090652,
      "reputation" : 4132,
      "user_id" : 1085360,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 73,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/853443fbfb1d61ba3793d3efe57e780d?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Chris Sim",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1085360/chris-sim"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 22,
    "last_activity_date" : 1485107165,
    "last_edit_date" : 1495540977,
    "creation_date" : 1438945641,
    "answer_id" : 31876250,
    "question_id" : 22756153,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>These steps can really help you:</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><p>If you didn't install any server you have to do these steps:</p>\n\n<p>Menu <em>Window</em> → <em>Preferences</em> → <em>Expend Server</em> → <em>Runtime environment</em> → <em>Add</em> → choose a name and then choose the Apache server path that you already installed on your PC (you can press download and install too) → <kbd>Finish</kbd> → <kbd>OK</kbd></p></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>Ref# <a href=\"http://help.eclipse.org/juno/index.jsp?topic=%2Forg.eclipse.jst.server.ui.doc.user%2Ftopics%2Ftwtomprf.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">for more information, click here</a></p>\n\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li><p>Add the Tomcat server:</p>\n\n<p><em>Project Properties</em> → <em>Java Build Path</em> → <em>Add Library</em> → Select \"Server Runtime\" from the list* → <em>Next</em> → Select \"Apache Tomcat\" → <kbd>Finish</kbd></p></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>Ref# <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/26936848/the-superclass-javax-servlet-http-httpservlet-was-not-found-on-the-java-build?answertab=active#tab-top\">This answer</a></p>\n"
  }, {
